02:58.737 --> 03:08.674
Would you describe

02:58.737 --> 03:08.674
that? About this time, I caught sight of a Jap 
formation. Neil came on the radio, come on over

03:15.325 --> 03:17.849
here, here they are. I thought to myself, where in 
the hell is here? And started in on the bombers I

03:21.074 --> 03:23.378
saw. There were 14 in perfect V formation. 
Suddenly I caught sight of that usual cluster

03:26.063 --> 03:32.012
formation of Japanese fighters directly above 
the bombers and changed my mind. I had to get some

03:33.614 --> 03:35.036
altitude speed. I ended up making my first attempt 
on the fighters, and this one was head on. He caught

03:39.202 --> 03:42.808
fire before I closed in to the point where I had to 
pull up to miss him. I looked for another and

03:42.988 --> 03:48.576
reached up with a pad on the charging handle of a .50 
caliber gun." I had a tendency to do that every time

03:48.596 --> 03:53.483
I would knock a fighter down. Pat the gun. And so you 
were coming straight in on this one, and he was

03:57.248 --> 04:01.293
coming straight in at you. A lot of times this 
happened. And you hit him? Yeah. He didn't hit you?

04:10.384 --> 04:11.185
No. Again, I ended up in a head-on attack. They were 
equally as aggressive as we were. We headed

04:17.012 --> 04:20.497
straight at each other, each with all our guns 
blazing. At what... It seemed to be the last second

04:22.032 --> 04:27.158
he pulled up, and I had decided to do the same thing 
at the same time. This is the one I was telling you

04:27.358 --> 04:29.380
about a while ago. Oh, okay. It is more natural, 
G-force-wise, to pull up than to push over. I

04:35.247 --> 04:40.373
reacted, it seemed, unconsciously, as I shoved 
forward on a stick violently. As tight as my

04:40.393 --> 04:44.918
seatbelt was, and boy, did we put him tight in 
expectation of combat. My head hit the top of my

04:44.938 --> 04:46.680
canopy. We shot past each other, him above me. I 
rolled and pulled violently to the left,

04:49.370 --> 04:53.455
straining my head over backwards to pick him up. 
He, too, was inflamed. Yow! Two in less than three

04:56.379 --> 04:58.381
minutes. Now, this is, see how I'm getting them 
mixed up? This is the next day. Yeah. Now, this is

